<!doctype html>
<title>{{ league }} Season {{ season }} Standings</title>

<p>Data updated on {{ updated.strftime("%H:%M") }} UTC</p>

<p>
  In the first column, "L" or "H" indicates that this team is the top team of
  the Low or High division of their sub-league, respectively.<br />
  "*" means that this team is one of the top two highest winning teams not top
  of their division.
  "‚ñº" means that this is one of the bottom 4 teams in the entire league and
  will recieve an extra Will in the Election.
</p>
<p>
  In the last column, a "üèÜ" means that this team has clinched a playoff spot
  for their subleague, and will see a postseason birth unless Black Hole or
  Sun 2 weather causes them to drop out of this position.<br />
  Likewise, a "ü•≥" indicates that this team has been mathematically eliminated
  from the playoffs and entered Party Time.<br />
  A number in this column indicates the day after which this site estimates
  the team will enter one of the above states, depending on whether they are
  presently in the running for the postseason or not.
</p>

{% for subleague, teams in standings.items() %}
<div style="width: 50%; float: left;">
  <h2>{{ subleague }}</h2>
  <table style="width: 85%;">
    <tr>
      <th />
      <th />
      <th style="text-align: left;">Team Name</th>
      <th>Wins</th>
      <th>Record</th>
      <th>Quickest</th>
      <th>Estimate</th>
    </tr>
    {% for team in teams %}
    <tr>
      {% if team %}
      <td>{{ team[0] }}</td>
      <td style="text-align: right;">[{{ team[3] }}]</td>
      <td>{{ team[1] }}</td>
      <td style="text-align: center;">{{ "*" if team[5] else "" }}{{ team[6] }}</td>
      <td style="text-align: center;">{{ team[7] }}</td>
      <td style="text-align: center;">{{ team[8] }}</td>
      <td style="text-align: center;">{{ team[9] }}</td>
      {% endif %}
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </table>
</div>
{% endfor %}
